==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gladiator
<hw>Glad"i*a`tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr.
<ets>gladius</ets> sword. See <er>Glaive</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Originally, a swordplayer; hence, one who fought with weapons in
public, either on the occasion of a funeral ceremony, or in the arena,
for public amusement.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who engages in any fierce combat or
controversy.</def></p>

<p><ent>Gladiatorian</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Gladiatorial</ent>⟦br⟧
